# Design System

Before editing UI in `examples/web/` or `examples/android/`:

1. Read @docs/WEB_PROJECT_LAYOUT.md before moving site files or choosing publish paths (web stack)
2. Read @docs/DESIGN_GUIDE.md
3. Read generated tokens in `design-tokens/design-tokens.json` (source) — not hand-edit outputs

## Repository layout (web)

- **`docs/` is agent documentation only** — never the public website root
- **App source:** `examples/web/`; **published output:** `examples/web/dist/` via GitHub Actions
- Do not enable GitHub Pages "Deploy from `/docs`" — use the Actions workflow in `.github/workflows/pages.yml`

## Mandatory rules

- **Tokens:** Change `design-tokens/design-tokens.json` only; run `python3 scripts/sync-design-tokens.py`
- **No raw hex** in UI Kotlin/TS/CSS (except `design-tokens.css` and generated `Color.kt`)
- **No UI string literals** in Compose (`Text("...")`) or web `main.ts` innerHTML — use `stringResource` / `t()`
- **No copy in CSS** — no `content:` text, no user-facing strings in stylesheets
- **Theme toggle:** Preserve system / light / dark cycle; default `system`
- **Layout:** CSS logical properties (`margin-inline`, `text-align: start`); Compose `Start`/`End` alignment
- **FOSS Android:** No `com.google.android.gms`, Firebase, or proprietary SDKs

## Stack specifics

### Android Compose M3

- `GoldenPathTheme(themeMode) { }` wrapper required
- `MaterialTheme.colorScheme`, `MaterialTheme.typography`, `Dimens.kt` spacing
- Theme preference via `ThemePreferences` (DataStore)

### Web

- `var(--gp-*)` from `design-tokens.css`
- `initTheme()` + `createThemeToggle()` pattern
- Locales in `src/locales/*.json`

## Critique before merge

- Checklist rows use 🔲 / ✅ / ❌ (see `docs/DESIGN_GUIDE.md` agent checklist)
- Long translated strings still layout correctly?
- Dark and light modes both readable (contrast)?
- Toggle accessible (`contentDescription` / `aria-label` from i18n)?
